raise= 5 #indentifier is a name used to identify a variable, function, class, module or other object. It is a user defined name that can be used to store a value or reference to an object. In this case, raise is an identifier that is used to store the value 5. It is not a keyword because it is not reserved by python and can be used as a variable name.
print("raise" , raise) # here raise is an identifier and it is used to store the value 5. It is not a keyword because it is not reserved by python and can be used as a variable name.